Washington â€“ CNN reported on Thursday that U.S. President Donald Trump is seriously considering cutting 250 million dollar the U.S. is providing in military assistance to Ukraine. The CNN made the reports citing multiple sources familiar with the matter. According to CNN, on Wednesday Politico reported that the issue of military assistance to Ukraine was under review, with funds for Ukraine being reserved. It said the publication added that Defence Secretary Mark Esper and National Security Adviser John Bolton were among the officials dealing with the issue. CNN also said the U.S. announced in June that it would provide Ukraine with an additional 250 million dollars in funds to help the country boost its military might. Earlier, Politico reported, citing a senior administration official that U.S. President had asked his national security team to review the military assistance program to Ukraine to ensure the funding is being used in the U.S. interests. (Sputnik/NAN)